Module 24 – The Pro Se Trap — Escape with Format 🪤📝

Core Message

Format can turn a rejection into a filing the court can’t easily block.

⸻

Lesson Introduction

Procedural traps for pro se litigants often hinge on format — missing sections, mislabeled documents, or informal language.

⸻

Teaching Block

1. Mirror Accepted Filings
	•	Copy the structure of a winning attorney-filed motion.

2. Overcomply
	•	Include more than the minimum required sections.

3. Preempt Objections
	•	Add jurisdiction, relief, and certificate sections even if not required.

⸻

Real-World Illustration

A refiled motion that mirrored attorney format was accepted after the original was rejected.

⸻

Assignment Prompt

Task:
Choose a motion type and draft its skeleton format.

⸻

Model Answer (Sample)

Caption → Introduction → Statement of Facts → Argument → Relief → Certificate of Service

⸻

Reflection Summary

Format is both shield and key.

⸻

Visual Pairing

Image Concept:
A skeleton key made of document sections. Caption:
“Format Unlocks the Court.”
